              <th data-sort="dining">Dining Out</th>
              <th data-sort="transport">Transport</th>
              <th data-sort="internet">Internet</th>
              <th data-sort="coworking">Coworking</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody id="table-body"></tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How do you compare cost of living between two cities?</h3>
        <p>Select two cities from the dropdown menus to see a side-by-side breakdown of rent, groceries, dining out, local transport, internet, and coworking costs. The tool calculates total monthly budgets and shows the percentage difference between the two cities.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is included in the monthly budget calculation?</h3>
        <p>The monthly budget includes 1-bedroom apartment rent in the city center, estimated monthly groceries, 20 restaurant meals, a local public transport pass, home internet, and a coworking space membership. These represent typical expenses for a digital nomad or remote worker.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Which city has the lowest cost of living for digital nomads?</h3>
        <p>Among popular nomad destinations, Da Nang (Vietnam), Chiang Mai (Thailand), and Cairo (Egypt) consistently rank as the most affordable cities, with total monthly budgets often under $900. However, cost should be balanced against factors like internet speed, safety, and visa accessibility.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How accurate is the cost of living data?</h3>
        <p>Data is aggregated from crowd-sourced cost of living databases and updated for 2026. All prices are in USD and may fluctuate based on exchange rates, seasonality, and individual lifestyle choices. The figures represent typical mid-range spending for a single remote worker.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What salary do I need to live comfortably in expensive cities like NYC or London?</h3>
        <p>In cities like New York or London, a comfortable remote worker budget ranges from $4,000 to $5,500 per month. Use the salary equivalent calculator above to see what your current salary would need to be in another city to maintain the same standard of living.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can I use this tool to plan my relocation budget?</h3>
        <p>Yes. The comparison tool shows detailed cost breakdowns across seven spending categories. Combined with the salary equivalent calculator, you can estimate how far your income stretches in different cities and plan your relocation or nomad itinerary accordingly.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related pages -->
    <section>
      <h2>Related Pages</h2>
      <div class="related-grid">
        <a href="/best-nomad-cities-2026" class="related-card">
          <h3>Best Nomad Cities 2026</h3>
